# Data Model

## Overview

The Enterprise Document Compliance Hub utilizes a metadata-driven data model implemented on SharePoint Online to manage controlled documents, review activities, ownership information, and compliance status throughout the document lifecycle.

The model was designed to support scalability, auditability, governance enforcement, and reporting requirements.

---

# Core Entity: Controlled Document

Represents a managed document within the compliance platform.

## Attributes

| Field            | Type     | Description                 |
| ---------------- | -------- | --------------------------- |
| DocumentID       | Text     | Unique document identifier  |
| Title            | Text     | Document title              |
| Category         | Choice   | Business classification     |
| Status           | Choice   | Current lifecycle status    |
| Version          | Text     | Current version number      |
| Owner            | Person   | Document owner              |
| Reviewer         | Person   | Assigned reviewer           |
| ReviewDate       | Date     | Most recent review date     |
| NextReviewDate   | Date     | Scheduled review date       |
| ComplianceStatus | Choice   | Compliance indicator        |
| CreatedDate      | DateTime | Initial creation date       |
| ModifiedDate     | DateTime | Last modification timestamp |

---

# Document Status Lifecycle

Documents transition through the following states:

```text
Draft
  ↓
In Review
  ↓
Approved
  ↓
Published
  ↓
Archived
```

Each transition is governed by workflow validation rules.

---

# Review Entity

Represents review activities performed against controlled documents.

## Attributes

| Field      | Type           | Description              |
| ---------- | -------------- | ------------------------ |
| ReviewID   | Text           | Unique review identifier |
| DocumentID | Lookup         | Related document         |
| Reviewer   | Person         | Assigned reviewer        |
| ReviewDate | DateTime       | Review completion date   |
| Outcome    | Choice         | Review result            |
| Comments   | Multiple Lines | Reviewer observations    |
| Status     | Choice         | Review status            |

---

# Ownership Entity

Tracks document accountability.

## Attributes

| Field      | Type   | Description             |
| ---------- | ------ | ----------------------- |
| OwnerID    | Text   | Unique owner identifier |
| UserName   | Text   | User display name       |
| Department | Text   | Business function       |
| Email      | Text   | Contact information     |
| Role       | Choice | Governance role         |

---

# Compliance Entity

Supports governance reporting and audit readiness.

## Attributes

| Field              | Type           | Description                  |
| ------------------ | -------------- | ---------------------------- |
| ComplianceID       | Text           | Compliance record identifier |
| DocumentID         | Lookup         | Related document             |
| ComplianceStatus   | Choice         | Current status               |
| LastAssessmentDate | Date           | Most recent assessment       |
| RiskLevel          | Choice         | Risk classification          |
| Findings           | Multiple Lines | Compliance observations      |

---

# Relationships

## Document → Review

Relationship:

```text
One Document
       │
       ▼
Many Reviews
```

Purpose:

Track multiple review cycles throughout the document lifecycle.

---

## Document → Owner

Relationship:

```text
One Owner
       │
       ▼
Many Documents
```

Purpose:

Establish accountability and governance ownership.

---

## Document → Compliance

Relationship:

```text
One Document
       │
       ▼
One Compliance Record
```

Purpose:

Maintain current compliance posture.

---

# Metadata Governance

The platform enforces standardized metadata management through:

* Controlled vocabularies
* Choice fields
* Validation rules
* Mandatory attributes
* Workflow-based updates

Benefits include:

* Improved searchability
* Reporting consistency
* Governance enforcement
* Data quality assurance

---

# Reporting Considerations

The data model was designed to support future reporting and analytics initiatives.

Example KPIs:

* Documents Due for Review
* Overdue Reviews
* Compliance Status Distribution
* Review Completion Rate
* Ownership Distribution
* Document Lifecycle Metrics

---

# Scalability Considerations

The model supports enterprise growth through:

* Metadata-driven architecture
* Reusable entity structures
* SharePoint indexing strategies
* Workflow automation integration
* Extensible compliance attributes

The resulting data model provides a scalable foundation for document governance, compliance management, and enterprise reporting.
